r a smaller mounted drawing. The second group, F 47-11-3-2, contains watercolour and drawing fragments of places in England and Europe, drawn after Mrs. Simcoe's return to England. Many of these have some identification. Differences in style suggest that some were not created by Mrs. Simcoe.\" .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Sub-Series> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> \"Sub-Series\" .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Elizabeth%20Simcoe%20Miscellaneous%20Sketches%20And%20Fragments%20Archival%20Description> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> \"Elizabeth Simcoe miscellaneous sketches and fragmentsÂ Archival Description\" .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Web%20Enabled%3A%20Y> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Elizabeth%20Simcoe%20Sketches> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#F%2047-11-3> <https://www.ica.org/standards/RiC/ontology#hasIdentifierType> <ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Current%20Reference%20Code> .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Elizabeth%20Simcoe%20Miscellaneous%20Sketches%20And%20Fragments-i1> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> \"Elizabeth Simcoe miscellaneous sketches and fragments-i1\" .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Walz> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#F%2047-11> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://www.ica.org/standards/RiC/ontology#Identifier> .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Elizabeth%20Simcoe%20Miscellaneous%20Sketches%20And%20Fragments> <https://www.ica.org/standards/RiC/ontology#history> \"Custodial History: The material in this sub-series was acquired in 1952 under the terms of a long-term loan agreement with 