 discovering what had happened in Walkerton, and why, and to make recommendations based on those findings. Part One involved a great deal of fact finding and included evidentiary hearings. Part Two of the Inquiry was broader in scope and dealt with policy issues related to safe drinking water. The primary purpose of Part Two was to make recommendations regarding Ontario's drinking water system.  The records in this series have been arranged into sub-series that broadly reflect Parts One and Two of the Inquiry, and also include general administrative records created by the Inquiry'sÂ   staff. Included in the sub-series are records connected with the hearings and meetings held by the Inquiry, commissioned research reports, correspondence, the reference database ofÂ   documents used by the Inquiry and the Inquiry's website.\" .\n<ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Textual%20Records> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://www.ica.org/standards/RiC/ontology#ContentType> .\n"

